This paper deals with privacy-preserving techniques for querying trajectory data, which is a common topic in the database community (cs.DB). The paper proposes a novel algorithm for ensuring differential privacy, which is a common topic in the security and cryptography community (cs.CR). The algorithm involves adding noise to the data and query in an adaptive manner, which requires machine learning techniques such as density estimation (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the accuracy and efficiency of the algorithm, which involves evaluating the trade-off between privacy and utility, a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and signal processing (cs.SI).
